column5: Sweet report Ron.  That second clip is great.  What a beautiful place.  Great fishing and great friends and seizures to boot, sounds like the perfect weekend to me.  Joey   Sheesh, if I keep this up, Paul will be an all knowing angler any day now  Joey
Excellent pics Ron! thanks for the boat ride!  looks like a great outing! Congrats
Awesome Ron...you deserve the leisure bud.  Great fish , looks like a lot of fun.  Matt
Good goin' fellers - good goin'!!
Looks like an awesome time out there and some really good looking pictures too.. Thanks for sharing

I didn't expect to see this report so soon Ron. But I'm glad that it's up. I didn't get to see a lot of your fish when they were caught, but the photos are almost just as good. The videos are awesome as well. The people viewing the videos have no idea how much current that you are running your boat in. And you sure know your way through there too. There's a few obstacles to avoid. It was great seeing you and Keith once again Ron. Sis and I enjoyed it immensely. Let's do it again some time.
great report, thanks for posting.
nice report and video
Very nice, well done!
Now that is just SICK! What a collection of super fish. And the scenery, WOW. Glad you all had a great time. Thanks for taking the time to post that, Ron. Your reports are always awaited on OFC.
What an awesome report!  Great friends, great scenery, great times, great fish!  You cant ask for more than that.  Congrats on a great trip.
An awesome report indeed! What a beautiful area and superb fish!  Thanks for the post.
as always, a great report
Is it that time of year again... lol.  Awesome gentlemen.  I'm soooo looking forward to heading out there next august for much the same.
Awesome report Ron.... Im thinking those are all the same fish though!!!
Great report Ron!   Good to see you here again.
Your subject title says it all...it truly is 'Brook Trout Fishing at It's Best!" and you guys are making it happen.
AWESOME PICS OF THOSE BROOKIES !!!!!!!!!
Thanks muchly Ron!      What a great adventure!  Look forward to bumping into you soon on Simcoe.  Take care!
i dont know much about brookies but those look like some trophy size very nice looking fish.
....Aw shucks, looky at what I missed out on....DANG!  Glad to see you had a good one Ron.
VERY VERY NICE!!!
Great report Ron. Was wondering when the itch to catch some monster brookies would grow strong enough to pull you away from the muskies again.  Thanks for the great report and pics.

WELL NICE SHOTS. WISH I WOULD HAVE BEEN INVITED BUT I GUESS I LIVE TO FAR FROM RON LOL OH YA RON ILL WALK OVER TO YOUR PLACE TONIGHT LOL GLAD TO SEE YOU HAD A GREAT TRIP AND GOOD YOU GOT TO SEE DAN C AND SIS TWO GREAT PEOPLE. I HOPE KIETH AND I WILL BE DOING A SPRING TRIP NEXT YEAR.
